gomodel:SYNGO_2002  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Endophilin was diffusely distributed throughout the entire presynaptic terminal (Fig. 7A-E).\"\n\nThe authors use conventional light microscopy and discover that \"endophilin is diffusely distributed throughout the presynaptic terminal and is not particularly enriched around the synaptic ribbon. All micrographs were obtained by conventional imaging\".. Experimental description: From legend to figure 7, \"Localization of endophilin in photoreceptor synapses of the mouse retina\"." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7806-5662" ;
        dc:date           "2017-12-06" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2002" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

